.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-LOGS" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.25" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-logs \- Print tracked service logs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose logs [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Print tracked service logs from a previous submit. Follow mode tails appended log data as it appears.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--job\-id\fR \fIJOB_ID\fR
Tracked Slurm job id to read instead of the latest recorded submission.
.TP
\fB--service\fR \fISERVICE\fR
Service name whose log should be printed.
.TP
\fB--follow\fR
Follow appended log output until interrupted.
.TP
\fB--lines\fR \fILINES\fR
Number of trailing log lines to show before follow mode begins. Default: 100.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose logs \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose logs \-f compose.yaml \-\-service app \-\-follow
hpc\-compose logs \-f compose.yaml \-\-job\-id 12345 \-\-lines 200
.fi
